properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 16 at 5:15AM AKST until January 18 at 8:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Very cold wind chills. Wind chills as low as 45 below
zero.

* WHERE...South Klondike Highway near White Pass.

* WHEN...Until 8 PM AKST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause frostbite
on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Temperatures have warmed into the teens
below zero. Therefore, wind chills have improved slightly.
However, despite not being as extreme as Tuesday night, wind
chills remain dangerous.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.
